</div>
</div></div>
<div id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-3" class="comp mntl-sc-block finance-sc-block-html mntl-sc-block-html">
<p>DSI is also known as the <a href="https://www.investopedia.com/terms/a/average-age-of-inventory.asp" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="1">average age of inventory</a>, days inventory outstanding (DIO), days in inventory (DII), days sales <em>in</em> inventory or days inventory and is interpreted in multiple ways. Indicating the liquidity of the inventory, the figure represents how many days a company’s current stock of inventory will last. Generally, a lower DSI is preferred as it indicates a shorter duration to clear off the inventory, though the average DSI varies from one industry to another.</p>
</div>
<div id="mntl-sc-block_1-0-4" class="comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-adslot mntl-block"><div id="mntl-block_4-0" class="comp mntl-block">
